---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Pricing — Claudient"
  description="Claudient is free forever. 295+ skills, 99+ agents, 5 languages, one command. Pro and Enterprise plans for teams that need private collections, custom skill development, and SLA-backed support."
  translatedLocales={[]}
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="container-page py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="pill mb-6">Free forever · Open source · Community</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-semibold tracking-tight leading-[1.05]">
        Start free. Scale with your team.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg md:text-xl max-w-2xl" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        The full Claudient knowledge base — 295+ skills, 99+ agents, hooks, MCP configs,
        and 5 languages — is free and open source, forever. Pro and Enterprise plans exist
        for teams that need private skill collections, custom development, and dedicated support.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing tiers -->
  <section
    class="border-y"
    style="background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated); border-color: var(--color-border);"
  >
    <div class="container-page py-16">
      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">

        <!-- Free -->
        <div class="card p-8 flex flex-col">
          <div class="mb-6">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Free</p>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-1">Free forever</h2>
            <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
              Everything in the open-source repo, no account required.
            </p>
          </div>

          <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8 flex-1">
            {[
              "All 295+ skills across every domain",
              "99+ pre-built agents",
              "Hooks, MCP configs, rules, workflows, prompts",
              "5 languages: EN, FR, DE, NL, ES",
              "npm install in 30 seconds",
              "AGPL-3.0 code license",
              "CC-BY-SA-4.0 content license",
              "Community contributions welcome",
            ].map((item) => (
              <li class="flex gap-3 text-sm">
                <span
                  class="mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 w-4 h-4 rounded-full inline-flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold"
                  style="background-color: var(--color-accent-soft); color: var(--color-accent);"
                >
                  ✓
                </span>
                <span>{item}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>

          <div>
            <div
              class="flex items-center px-3 py-2 rounded-md font-mono text-sm mb-4"
              style="background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);"
            >
              <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">$</span>&nbsp;npx claudient add all
            </div>
            <a href="/install/" class="btn-primary w-full text-center block">
              Get started free
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Pro -->
        <div
          class="card p-8 flex flex-col relative"
          style="border-color: var(--color-accent);"
        >
          <div
            class="absolute -top-3 left-8 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold"
            style="background-color: var(--color-accent); color: #fff;"
          >
            Coming soon
          </div>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Pro</p>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-1">Pro</h2>
            <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
              For teams that need private skills and dedicated rollout support. Pricing on request.
            </p>
          </div>

          <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8 flex-1">
            {[
              "Everything in Free",
              "Private skill collections (not open-sourced)",
              "Team onboarding and rollout support",
              "Priority issue resolution",
              "Custom skill development by Uitbreiden team",
            ].map((item) => (
              <li class="flex gap-3 text-sm">
                <span
                  class="mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 w-4 h-4 rounded-full inline-flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold"
                  style="background-color: var(--color-accent-soft); color: var(--color-accent);"
                >
                  ✓
                </span>
                <span>{item}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>

          <div>
            <a
              href="mailto:hello@uitbreiden.com?subject=Claudient%20Pro"
              class="btn-primary w-full text-center block"
            >
              Contact us
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Enterprise -->
        <div class="card p-8 flex flex-col">
          <div class="mb-6">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Enterprise</p>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-1">Enterprise</h2>
            <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
              For regulated industries and large teams that need SLA-backed service and compliance guidance.
            </p>
          </div>

          <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8 flex-1">
            {[
              "Everything in Pro",
              "SLA-backed support",
              "GDPR-compliant deployment guidance",
              "Custom MCP server development",
              "Dedicated Uitbreiden contact",
            ].map((item) => (
              <li class="flex gap-3 text-sm">
                <span
                  class="mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 w-4 h-4 rounded-full inline-flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold"
                  style="background-color: var(--color-accent-soft); color: var(--color-accent);"
                >
                  ✓
                </span>
                <span>{item}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>

          <div>
            <a
              href="mailto:hello@uitbreiden.com?subject=Claudient%20Enterprise"
              class="btn-ghost w-full text-center block"
            >
              Contact us
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="container-page py-16">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-10">Frequently asked questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Is it really free?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
            Yes. The entire Claudient library — every skill, agent, hook, MCP config, guide,
            workflow, and prompt — is available at no cost under open-source licenses. There is
            no trial period, no credit card, and no feature gating. Run
            <code class="px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono" style="background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">npx claudient add all</code>
            and you have everything.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="border-t pt-8"
          style="border-color: var(--color-border);"
        >
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Can I use this commercially?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
            Yes. The content (skills, agents, guides, etc.) is licensed under CC-BY-SA-4.0,
            which permits commercial use as long as you attribute Uitbreiden and share any
            derivative content under the same license. The tooling and site code is AGPL-3.0:
            free to use commercially, but if you run a modified version as a network service,
            you must release your modifications. Using skills locally inside Claude Code — the
            primary use case — carries no extra obligations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="border-t pt-8"
          style="border-color: var(--color-border);"
        >
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">What is the practical difference between AGPL and CC-BY-SA for me?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
            For most users there is no practical difference. If you install Claudient and use
            it with your own Claude Code setup, both licenses are satisfied automatically.
            The distinction matters only if you fork and redistribute: AGPL applies to the
            Astro site and hook scripts (share source if you host publicly), while CC-BY-SA
            applies to the markdown content files (attribute and share alike if you republish).
            Neither license restricts private internal use or prevents you from writing skills
            that are specific to your own organisation.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="border-t pt-8"
          style="border-color: var(--color-border);"
        >
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Can Uitbreiden build custom skills for us?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
            Yes. Custom skill development is available on the Pro and Enterprise plans.
            Uitbreiden can build skills for proprietary workflows, internal tooling,
            regulated industry requirements, or any domain not yet covered by the community
            library. These private skills stay yours — they are not contributed back to the
            open-source repo unless you choose to. Email
            <a
              href="mailto:hello@uitbreiden.com"
              style="color: var(--color-accent);"
            >hello@uitbreiden.com</a>
            to discuss scope.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Community CTA -->
  <section
    class="border-y"
    style="background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated); border-color: var(--color-border);"
  >
    <div class="container-page py-16">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">Build it with the community</h2>
        <p class="text-sm mb-8" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
          Every skill lives in one markdown file. Contributing is fast, the bar is low,
          and merged skills get featured across the site. If you have domain expertise
          that Claude Code should have, write it down.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a href="/contribute/" class="btn-primary">Contribute a skill</a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/uitbreiden/claudient"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="btn-ghost"
          >
            GitHub repository
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <section class="container-page py-20">
    <div class="max-w-xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">Get started in 30 seconds</h2>
      <p class="text-sm mb-6" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        One command installs every skill, agent, hook, and MCP config in the library.
        No account. No setup beyond a Node.js environment.
      </p>
      <div
        class="flex items-center px-4 py-3 rounded-md font-mono text-sm mb-6 w-fit"
        style="background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);"
      >
        <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">$</span>&nbsp;npx claudient add all
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
        <a href="/install/" class="btn-primary">Installation guide</a>
        <a
          href="mailto:hello@uitbreiden.com?subject=Claudient%20Pro"
          class="btn-ghost"
        >
          Talk to Uitbreiden
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
